<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Privacy Policy | The Federal Disability Review</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Privacy Policy for The Federal Disability Review, LLC." />
  
<style>
  :root {
    --navy: #0c1526;
    --cream: #f5f3ee;
    --white: #ffffff;
    --gold: #c8a34b;
    --burgundy: #7c0d2b;
    --text: #101827;
    --muted: #5f6676;
    --line: #d9d4ca;
    --max: 920px;
    --serif: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', serif;
    --sans: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;
  }
  * { box-sizing: border-box; }
  body {
    margin: 0;
    background: var(--cream);
    color: var(--text);
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.75;
  }
  .topline {
    background: #08101e;
    color: var(--gold);
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: .095em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 8px 16px;
  }
  header {
    background: var(--navy);
    color: white;
    padding: 54px 24px;
    text-align: center;
  }
  header h1 {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: clamp(34px, 5vw, 52px);
    line-height: 1.1;
    margin: 0 0 12px;
    color: white;
  }
  header p {
    max-width: 680px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,.78);
  }
  main {
    width: min(var(--max), calc(100% - 42px));
    margin: 0 auto;
    background: var(--white);
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    padding: 42px;
    transform: translateY(-24px);
  }
  h2 {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    color: var(--navy);
    font-size: 24px;
    margin: 34px 0 10px;
  }
  h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  p, li { color: var(--muted); }
  ul { padding-left: 22px; }
  a { color: var(--burgundy); font-weight: 700; }
  .back {
    display: inline-flex;
    margin-top: 22px;
    color: var(--burgundy);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 900;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: .06em;
    font-size: 11px;
  }
  footer {
    background: var(--navy);
    color: rgba(255,255,255,.7);
    text-align: center;
    padding: 28px 20px;
    font-size: 12px;
  }
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    main { padding: 28px 22px; }
  }
</style>

</head>
<body>
  <div class="topline">The Federal Disability Review, LLC</div>
  <header>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p>Effective Date: May 2026</p>
  </header>

  <main>
    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>The Federal Disability Review, LLC (“TFDR,” “we,” “our,” or “us”) respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect information submitted through our website, contact forms, consultation requests, and related communications.</p>

    <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>We may collect personal information you voluntarily provide, including your name, email address, phone number, agency or employment information, and a brief description of your situation. We may also collect standard website usage information, such as browser type, device information, and general analytics data.</p>

    <h2>Sensitive Information</h2>
    <p>Please do not submit Social Security numbers, medical records, financial account information, or highly sensitive documents through the website contact form. Initial consultation forms are intended for general intake only.</p>

    <h2>How We Use Information</h2>
    <p>Information you provide may be used to respond to inquiries, evaluate whether TFDR may be able to assist you, schedule consultations, provide requested services, improve website functionality, and maintain internal business records.</p>

    <h2>Information Sharing</h2>
    <p>We do not sell your personal information. We may share information only when necessary to operate our business, comply with legal obligations, protect our rights, or with your consent. If a referral to an attorney or other professional is discussed, information will not be shared without your permission.</p>

    <h2>Email and Communications</h2>
    <p>By submitting a form or contacting TFDR, you consent to receive communications related to your inquiry. You may request that we stop contacting you at any time by emailing <a href="mailto:support@thefederaldisabilityreview.com">support@thefederaldisabilityreview.com</a>.</p>

    <h2>Data Security</h2>
    <p>We use reasonable safeguards to protect information submitted to us. However, no website, email system, or online transmission method is completely secure. You should avoid sending highly sensitive information through unsecured channels.</p>

    <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p>Our website may use third-party tools for hosting, forms, analytics, scheduling, or payment processing. Those providers may collect or process information according to their own privacy policies.</p>

    <h2>Data Retention</h2>
    <p>We retain information only as long as reasonably necessary for business, legal, operational, or recordkeeping purposes.</p>

    <h2>Your Choices</h2>
    <p>You may request access, correction, or deletion of information you have provided by contacting us at <a href="mailto:support@thefederaldisabilityreview.com">support@thefederaldisabilityreview.com</a>. We may retain certain records when required for legal or legitimate business reasons.</p>

    <h2>Children’s Privacy</h2>
    <p>Our services are intended for adults and are not directed to children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children.</p>

    <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Updates will be posted on this page with a revised effective date.</p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>Questions about this Privacy Policy may be sent to <a href="mailto:support@thefederaldisabilityreview.com">support@thefederaldisabilityreview.com</a>.</p>

    <a class="back" href="index.html">← Back to Home</a>
  </main>

  <footer>© 2026 The Federal Disability Review, LLC. All rights reserved.</footer>
</body>
</html>
